description.text: Submodel containing techical data to the asset.
General information refers to the basic details about a product that would identify and describe it without getting into the detailed technical specifications.

A technical property generally refers to a characteristic or attribute that defines or describes the technical aspects of an object, system, material, or process. These properties are usually measurable or quantifiable and are critical in determining how something will function or perform in a specific context.
The unique identification number assigned to a specific product.
The unique identification number assigned to a specific stock.
The distance that the valve can move from its fully closed position to its fully open position.
The amount of fluid that can leak through the valve when it is fully closed.
The nominal diameter of the valve, which is the size of the opening through which the fluid flows.
The flow coefficient of the valve, which is a measure of its flow capacity.
The temperature range in which the valve can safely operate.
The relationship between the valve's opening and the flow rate of the fluid.
The ratio of the maximum to minimum controllable flow rate of the valve.
The maximum pressure that the valve can safely withstand during operation.
The type of material used to construct the body of the valve.
The material used for the internal components of the valve.
The maximum pressure that a valve can withstand.
